description: In many ways, the fact that Roots Reggae from the 70s and 80s is still so relevant today is shocking and saddening. The need to explain to society that Black Lives Matter may be exhausting at times, but this is certainly fuel for the fire that can help to keep fighting for equal rights and justice.
